    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the author's intent in its canonical context. The movements below trace the psalm's argument through its three cycles: the ground of refuge (71:1-8), the crisis and counter-resolve (71:9-16), and the full-throated vow of proclamation (71:17-24). Where the Hebrew changes the shade of an English word, a brief note follows the interpretation as supplement.",
